      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: implement shadow-logger plugin for memory system",
        "body": "## Description\nThis PR implements the `shadow-logger` plugin, which provides the Layer 1 (Episodic Memory) of the new multi-layered memory system for OpenClaw. \n\nThe plugin \"taps\" into the OpenClaw internal hook system to capture all incoming (`message:received`) and outgoing (`message:sent`) messages. These messages are then logged to a Supabase database, enabling asynchronous distillation into semantic memory layers later.\n\n## Technical Details\n- **Implementation:** A new OpenClaw plugin in `extensions/shadow-logger/`.\n- **Integration:** Uses `registerInternalHook` to listen to message events.\n- **Storage:** Uses Supabase for persistent storage of raw dialogues.\n- **Schema:**\n    - `dialogues` table: Stores raw message payloads, including conversation context and metadata.\n\n## Documentation\nDetailed technical specification can be found here: [OpenClaw Memory System - Technical Implementation Specification](https://app.notion.com/p/OpenClaw-Memory-System-Technical-Implementation-Specification-37df97eb93ff81538079da4bfb131619)\n\n## Checklist\n- [x] Implement `shadow-logger.plugin.ts`\n- [x] Configure plugin manifest and package\n- [x] Ensure plugin is discoverable",
